<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
The perithecia of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. vescum" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="vescum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. vescum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are smaller than in related species and ascospores are different in shape and size. This species was treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. olivaceum" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="olivaceum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. olivaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by various authors (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b68-094" author="Griffin, HD" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="689 - 718" refId="B11" refString="Griffin, HD, 1968. The genus Ceratocystis in Ontario. Canadian Journal of Botany 46: 689 - 718" title="The genus Ceratocystis in Ontario." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b68-094" volume="46" year="1968">Griffin 1968</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b74-222" author="Olchowecki, A" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="1675 - 1711" refId="B39" refString="Olchowecki, A, Reid, J, 1974. Taxonomy of the genus Ceratocystis in Manitoba. Canadian Journal of Botany 52: 1675 - 1711" title="Taxonomy of the genus Ceratocystis in Manitoba." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b74-222" volume="52" year="1974">Olchowecki and Reid 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Upadhyay, HP" journalOrPublisher="Molecular biology and evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" refId="B54" refString="Upadhyay, HP, 1981. A monograph of Ceratocystis and Ceratocystiopsis. University of Georgia Press." title="A monograph of Ceratocystis and Ceratocystiopsis. University of Georgia Press." year="1981">Upadhyay 1981</bibRefCitation>
). However, the sequences produced by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b93-148" author="Hausner, G" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="1249 - 1265" refId="B14" refString="Hausner, G, Reid, J, Klassen, GR, 1993. On the phylogeny of Ophiostoma, Ceratocystis s.s., and Microascus, and relationships within Ophiostoma based on partial ribosomal DNA sequences. Canadian Journal of Botany 71: 1249 - 1265" title="On the phylogeny of Ophiostoma, Ceratocystis s. s., and Microascus, and relationships within Ophiostoma based on partial ribosomal DNA sequences." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b93-148" volume="71" year="1993">Hausner et al. (1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b00-068" author="Hausner, G" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="903 - 916" refId="B15" refString="Hausner, G, Reid, J, Klassen, GR, 2000. On the phylogeny of members of Ceratocystis s.s. and Ophiostoma that possess different anamorphic states, with emphasis on the anamorph genus Leptographium, based on partial ribosomal DNA sequences. Canadian Journal of Botany 78: 903 - 916" title="On the phylogeny of members of Ceratocystis s. s. and Ophiostoma that possess different anamorphic states, with emphasis on the anamorph genus Leptographium, based on partial ribosomal DNA sequences." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b00-068" volume="78" year="2000">2000</bibRefCitation>
), confirmed by our results, showed that the two species are distinct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
